\par\pard\plain \tx-720\sl240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Relationship}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0  tab on the }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Character}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0  form describes significant character-to-character relationships.}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Relationships are made when two people with a different set of values and often varying personalities come together. Relationships in fiction (and in life)  can be a source of conflict.}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx-720\sl240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Most stories involve interactions between characters: adversarial, social, familial, romantic. A character in a relationship is distinct from a character as an individual; the relationship is a dynamic. Characters in a relationship behave differently when they\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92re together- a sort of role.}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 This tab is only one half  of the relationship; go to the Relation character  to define  the other half. Be aware that the two sides of a relationship seldom have the same dynamic.}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Create a new Relationship}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Click on this button to add a new relationship:}
